
@startuml
skinparam backgroundColor White
skinparam classAttributeIconColor Blue

class Museum {
  -name: String
  -locations: List<Location>
}

class Location {
  -name: String
  -exhibitions: List<Exhibition>
}

class Exhibition {
  -title: String
  -startDate: Date
  -endDate: Date
  -coordinator: Employee
  -items: List<ExhibitionItem>
}

class Employee {
  -name: String
  -role: String
  -coach: Employee
}

class ExhibitionItem {
  -description: String
  -piecesRequested: List<PieceRequest>
}

class PieceRequest {
  -piece: Piece
  -collector: Collector
  -status: String
}

class Collector {
  -name: String
  -pieces: List<Piece>
}

class Piece {
  -title: String
  -artist: String
  -type: String
  -availability: Boolean
}

class CoachingRelationship {
  -junior: Employee
  -senior: Employee
}

' Associations
Museum "1" --> "n" Location
Location "1" --> "n" Exhibition
Exhibition "1" --> "1" Employee : coordinator
Employee "1" --> "0..1" Employee : coach
Exhibition "1" --> "n" ExhibitionItem
ExhibitionItem "1" --> "n" PieceRequest
PieceRequest "1" --> "1" Piece
PieceRequest "1" --> "1" Collector
Collector "1" --> "n" Piece

' Note: Coaching relationship is modeled as a separate class and association
Employee "1" --> "n" CoachingRelationship
Employee "1" --> "n" CoachingRelationship
@enduml

---

### Explanation of Key Elements in the Diagram:

- **Museum**: Contains multiple **Locations**.
- **Location**: Can host multiple **Exhibitions**.
- **Exhibition**: Has a **Coordinator (Employee)**, and a list of **ExhibitionItems**.
- **Employee**: May have a **Coach** (another employee), and may be assigned to one or more **Exhibitions**.
- **ExhibitionItem**: Represents an item that should be part of an exhibition. For each such item, several **PieceRequests** can be made.
- **PieceRequest**: Tracks which **Piece** is requested from which **Collector**.
- **Collector**: Holds a collection of **Pieces**.
- **Piece**: A specific artwork with title, artist, type, and availability status.

